        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-19 13:26:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nKrzysztof, can you confirm that all of these changes have been validated in a local environment? We are close to code freeze and have already spent a considerable time debugging an issue that was traced back to one of the refactored code submits, so we need to be very cautious at this stage. Please confirm that these changes have been validated in a local environment with a running instance of APPC. Thanks.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "0b29d5bd360637e9482cd9d631ff09dd172cac10",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2731,
          "name": "KK",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "krzysztof.kurczewski@nokia.com",
          "username": "kurczews"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-19 14:28:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nWhat I can confirm is that:\n\n\n* I wrote unit tests before changing logic and then proceed with refactoring\n\n\n* I have successfully run APPC after changes with this instruction:\nhttps://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Building+and+Running+APPC+Docker+Images\n\n\n\nHowever I did not found any other instruction how to test APPC in separation. Sending requests from API fails because of missing data, probably provided by other components. Sadly I don't have capability to run full ONAP environment.\n\n\nIf this is insufficient I can't help much more than abandon changes until freeze ends, but that doesn't solve problem of local testing.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
